\f0\b \cf0 Data Preparation subdirectory:
\f1\b0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\pardirnatural\qj\partightenfactor0
\cf0 In addition to the analyses carried out in the folders for each manuscript, the \ul Prepare Separate Dataframes for Cohort 1.R\ulnone  script pulls data from the main CSV files with raw data. This divides the data into smaller CSV files broken down by speaker type (heritage versus L2 learner) and age group (2nd grade, 4th/5th grades, 7th/8th grades) from the first round of data collection in 2023 only (cohort 1, session 1). We used this coding loop to prepare CSV files for manuscripts and presentations that only reflected the initial data collection session.\
\
For subsequent analyses incorporating data from additional cohorts or sessions, we used the \ul Prepare Master Data File.R\ulnone  files to create structure-specific datasets and a master CSV file with all of the necessary calculations with which to run correlations and create figures that incorporated more than the first cohort and session (that is, all subsequent data collected).\
\
